ss=\"ico-feedback\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-feedback\"></use></svg><span class=\"zDocsFeedbackButtonText\"> Feedback</span></span></div></div><div class=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><button aria-label=\"Show topic actions\" data-toggle=\"dropdown\" id=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-ellipsis-h\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-ellipsis-h\"></use></svg></button><div class=\"dropdown-menu zDocsDropdownMenu zDocsTopicActionsMobileDropdown dropdown-menu-right\"></div></div><div style=\"flex-basis: 100%; height: 0px;\"></div><ul class=\"zDocsTopicPageDetails\"><li class=\"zDocsTopicPageDate css-cinqea\">Last Updated<span class=\"css-cinqea\">Jan 08, 2024</span></li><li class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryDetailsItem\"><button class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryButton\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-topic-summary\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-topic-summary\"></use></svg>Summarize</button></li><li class=\"spacer\" role=\"presentation\"></li><div class=\"zDocsLabelWrapper\"><ul><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: Uniface\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=prod_uniface\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>Uniface</a></li><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: 10.4\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=uniface_10.4\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>10.4</a></li></ul></div></ul></header><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBody\" data-prismjs-copy=\"Copy\" data-prismjs-copy-error=\"Copy failed! Use Ctrl + C instead.\" data-prismjs-copy-success=\"Copied!\"><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBodyContent\" dir=\"ltr\"><div id=\"zDocsAiSummaryContaineruniface_104sqn1704693127922.html\"></div><div><article class=\"hascomments\" data-page=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/sqn1704693127922.html\" id=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/sqn1704693127922.html\"><main role=\"main\"><article aria-labelledby=\"ariaid-title1\" class=\"dita\" id=\"fii1665702653163\" role=\"article\">\n<h1 class=\"title topictitle1\" id=\"ariaid-title1\">\n      Session Services\n </h1>\n<div class=\"body conbody\"><p class=\"shortdesc\">Session service components define task-specific behavior for components in the presentation tier. For example, a user enters information to update a customer using a dynamic server page, but a session service is called to actually perform the data update.\n </p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"fii1665702653163__p_d11060e1_d11061e1_d11062e1\">Session services can be used to:</p>\n<ul class=\"ul\">\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"fii1665702653163__li_d5171e1_d5172e1_d5173e1\">Manage referential integrity and transactions\n </li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"fii1665702653163__li_d5174e1_d5175e1_d5176e1\">Implement behavior and operations involving one or more entities\n </li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"fii1665702653163__li_d5177e1_d5178e1_d5179e1\">Expose disconnected XML record sets to client components\n </li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"fii1665702653163__li_d5180e1_d5181e1_d5182e1\">Maintain the server side of the conversational state\n </li>\n</ul>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"fii1665702653163__p_d11063e1_d11064e1_d11065e1\">Session service components are usually stateless, so Uniface provides special triggers for setting and getting state information. Component operations on session services exchange data as disconnected XML record sets, which are described by Document Type Definitions (DTDs). These DTDs are automatically generated if the session service components are generated by Uniface rather than created manually.</p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"fii1665702653163__p_d11066e1_d11067e1_d11068e1\">Technically, there is almost no difference between a session service and a regular service. To create a session service, create a Service and change the <span class=\"ph uicontrol\">Component Type</span> to <code class=\"ph codeph\">4 (Session Service)</code> and set the value of the <code class=\"ph codeph\">&lt;$cmpStatemanagedBy&gt;</code> (<span class=\"ph uicontrol\">State Managed By</span>) property.</p>\n</div>\n</article></main></article>\n</div></div><div class=\"contentPlaceholder\" style=\"height: 500px;\"><div class=\"contentContainer zDocsSideBoxes\"><div><h5 aria-level=\"5\" class=\"css-g931ng\">Related Links</h5><ul><li><a class=\"css-ettsdk\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/cik1665702689127.html\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-related-link\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-related-link\"></use></svg>State Managed By</a><p>Sets the value of the &lt;$cmpStatemanagedBy&gt; constant, which specifies the mechanism used to save state information for the component.</p></li><li><a class=\"css-ettsdk\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/aau1665702621803.html\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-related-link\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-related-link\"></use></svg>&lt;$cmpStateManagedBy&gt;</a><p>The &lt;$cmpStatemanagedBy&gt; constant determines how component state is managed for the server page or session service.</p></li></ul></div></div></div></div><div class=\"bottomFeedback\"><div aria-labelledby=\"bottomFeedbackText\" class=\"bottomFeedbackContent\" role=\"group\"><span class=\"bottomFeedbackText\" id=\"bottomFeedbackText\">Was this topic helpful?</span><div class=\"bottomFeedbackButtonGroup\"><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_5756289\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-up\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-up\"></use></svg><span>Like</span></a><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_5756289\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-down\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-down\"></use></svg><span>Dislike</span></a></div></div></div><div style=\"position: fixed; bottom: 170px; right: 70px; cursor: pointer; transition-duration: 0.2s; transition-timing-function: linear; transition-delay: 0s; z-index: 3; opacity: 0; visibility: hidden; transition-property: opacity, visibility;\"><button aria-label=\"Scroll to top\" class=\"zDocsScrollTopBtn\" data-tooltip-content=\"Scroll to top\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsBackToTopToolTip\" id=\"zDocsScrollToTop\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-next\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-next\"></use></svg></button></div></body></html>", "text": "Session Services Add to My Topics Add selected topic and subtopics Add Topic & Subtopics with topic head Add entire publication Watch Download PDF Save selected topic Save selected topic and subtopics Save entire publication Share Email Link Copy Link Feedback Last Updated Jan 08, 2024 Summarize Uniface 10.4 Session Services Session service components define task-specific behavior for components in the presentation tier. For example, a user enters information to update a customer using a dynamic server page, but a session service is called to actually perform the data update. Session services can be used to: Manage referential integrity and transactions Implement behavior and operations involving one or more entities Expose disconnected XML record sets to client components Maintain the server side of the conversational state Session service components are usually stateless, so Uniface provides special triggers for setting and getting state information. Component operations on session services exchange data as disconnected XML record sets, which are described by Document Type Definitions (DTDs). These DTDs are automatically generated if the session service components are generated by Uniface rather than created manually. Technically, there is almost no difference between a session service and a regular service. To create a session service, create a Service and change the Component Type to 4 (Session Service) and set the value of the <$cmpStatemanagedBy> ( State Managed By ) property. Related Links State Managed By Sets the value of the <$cmpStatemanagedBy> constant, which specifies the mechanism used to save state information for the component. <$cmpStateManagedBy> The <$cmpStatemanagedBy> constant determines how component state is managed for the server page or session service. Was this topic helpful? Like Dislike"}